<TITLE> Dhaka residents stage colourful Eid rallies </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 22 (bdnews24.com)--Dhakabashi, a citizen's organisation, held a festive Eid celebration rally despite the continuous drizzle that prevailed through Tuesday. Children and people of all ages in colourful clothing participated in the rally displaying the traditional attributes of Bangladesh like snake charmers, horse carriages. The rally started off from the Shishu Academy and traveled through Doyel Chattar and crossed the High Court to end at the Academy. Before the start of the rally, a session discussed various problems facing the city like the destruction of the historical sites and buildings due to the lack of proper maintenance. The government was urged to take necessary steps to preserve them. State minister of law Kamrul Islam participated in the rally as chief guest. Bangladesh Workers' Party president Rashed Khan Menon MP, former advisor Rasheda K Chowdhury and former chairman of the Privatisation Commission Inam Ahmed Chowdhury also attended the rally. Old Dhaka's 69 ward's 'Nagarbashi' also staged a colourful rally. The rally ended at the National Press Club where they demanded a traffic gridlock-free Old Dhaka and unpolluted Buriganga river. bd
